            "title": "Plus operator",
            "id": 82583,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Para combinar dos conjuntos de datos, como los que están en <code>dataset_1</code> y <code>dataset_2</code>, usamos los nombres de las listas y el operador <code>+</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"dataset_1 = [\" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"dataset_2 = [\" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(dataset_1 + dataset_2)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"48\" endIndex=\"57\" /><option startIndex=\"58\" endIndex=\"59\" /><option startIndex=\"60\" endIndex=\"69\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>dataset_1</code> seguido de <code>+</code> y finalmente <code>dataset_2</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Appended at the end",
            "id": 82584,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
