            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>También podemos usar <code>+</code> para combinar listas que contienen diferentes tipos de valores, como el numérico <code>seats</code> y el booleano <code>taken</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"seats = [\" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"taken = [\" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"False\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(seats + taken)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"5\" /><option startIndex=\"18\" endIndex=\"23\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"[1, 2, 3, True, True, False]\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>seats</code> seguido de <code>taken</code>.</p></body></html>"
